<pre > Cherry MX Blue have tactile feedback with a click (noisy); good for typing. Cherry MX Brown are inbetween Blue and Red in style and tactile; Cherry MX Clear switches have soft tactile feedback (with no click). Cherry MX Black are linear switches (no feedback); good for gaming. Cherry MX Red are linear (less noise no click) but more squishy; </pre >
=== Mouse ===
if the usb mouse is non-functional put a usb pendrive in before or add the following to user-startup in '''s''' drawer/folder/directory
sys:prefs/trident NOGUI > NIL:
